@NODE "Intro"

Introducing AD516-AHI
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  For quite some time I have wanted to be able to use my AD516 Card with
  AmigaAmp. Unfortunately there was no AHI driver available that allowed
  for playback from AmigaAmp through the AD516 card, and so I lived with
  the less than stellar sound from the native audio hardware. Then, about
  three months ago, I was in need of a quick and efficient way to record my
  vinyl records to MP3 files. Unfortunately, the process I had used for
  individual songs would require too much time and disk space for entire
  albums, so I set about trying to find a way to pipe the output from
  Studio 16 directly to an MP3 encoder. It just wouldn't work. The Studio 16
  software will only write to an actual disk drive volume. The only option
  left was to figure out how to address the AD516 hardware directly. I spent
  the next three weeks experimenting with the hardware and finally discovered
  how to play and record through direct use of the AD516 hardware. I compiled
  this information and put it up on Aminet for those who might be interested.
  I was also hoping that someone would become inspired to write an AHI
  driver, but so far no one has. Well now that I am on Christmas break, I
  have some free time, so I decided to give it a shot.
@ENDNODE

