@NODE "Requirements"

System Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  À An Amiga with at least a 68020 processor

  À A Sunrize AD516 audio card

  À Version 3.01 of the Sunrize Studio 16 software

  À AHI version 4
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install"

The Installation Procedure
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  In this archive you will find the following files

  devs/AHI/AD516.audio
  devs/AudioModes/AD516

  Simply copy these two files into their respective directories in DEVS:
  using your favorite directory utility, or from a shell type:

  cd AD516-AHI
  copy devs DEVS: all


  Once the files have been copied, run the AHI preferences program and
  select the desired audio mode for each AHI unit.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Notes"

Notes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  AD516-AHI requires that version 3.01 of the Studio 16 software be
  properly installed. It doesn't require the Studio 16 environment, but it
  does require the AD516 DSP operating code that is embedded in the
  AD516Handler file. I have debated over whether or not I should just
  include the DSP code in my driver, and I ended up decided on loading it
  from the handler file on startup. I realize that Sunrize has been out of
  business for quite some time, and that probably, no one would care if I
  include their DSP code in my software, but I am not intimately familiar
  with copyright laws, and want to avoid getting into any kind of legal
  trouble. And besides, anyone who has an AD516 card in their computer must
  have the Studio 16 software installed since it is the only software that
  works with the card.

  Limitations
  À Supports only one AD516 card
  À The driver will stop at the first AD516 card it finds
  À Disallows concurrent use of the driver by multiple applications
  À The DSP is not used for mixing or effects

  Tested Applications
  À  Advanced AHI HD-Recorder version 1.6
  À  AHI-SoundDT
  À  AmigaAmp PPC version 2.9 BETA-1
  À  MamePPC version 35.12 (sound is still terrible)
  À  NewTracker version 3.56 AHIr2
  À  Soundprobe version 1.76
  À  ShapeShifter version 3.10
@ENDNODE

